## 2. Hard Blocks ({{ project.name }} — project-specific)

- ❌ **NEVER push to remote.** Local commits only. `git push` to upstream remotes is forbidden unless the task explicitly says otherwise.
- ❌ **NEVER write functions >{{ cq.max_function_lines | default(75) }} lines** without a comment justifying why decomposition would harm clarity.
- ❌ **NEVER scope-creep.** If you discover an unrelated bug or refactor opportunity, log it via `kanban_comment` (so we don't lose the signal) and stay on your task.
- ❌ **NEVER mock services we run locally.** Use real implementations against test-suffix collections / `tmp_path` fixtures (see §5 Anti-Mock Philosophy).
